'''''Britain's Lost Masterpieces''''' is a factual [[BBC Four]] television series that aims to uncover overlooked [[art]] masterpieces in public collections, in conjunction with [[Art UK]].<ref name="Home">{{cite web|title=Britain's Lost Masterpieces - BBC Four|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b096mhvs|publisher=[[BBC]]|accessdate=29 September 2017}}</ref><ref name="Jordaens">{{cite web|title=BBC Four’s Britain’s Lost Masterpieces discovers rare painting by 17th Century master Jacob Jordaens|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/latestnews/2016/britains-lost-masterpieces-jacob-jordaens|publisher=[[BBC]]|accessdate=29 September 2017}}</ref> It is presented by [[Bendor Grosvenor]] and a companion. In series 1 this was [[Jacky Klein]]; in series 2, [[Emma Dabiri]]. Programmes also feature the [[art restoration|art restorer]], [[Simon Rollo Gillespie]].
== Series 1 ==
Series one, comprising three episodes, aired in September—October 2016.<ref name="S1">{{cite web|title=Series 1, Britain's Lost Masterpieces - Episode guide - BBC Four|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b07xjtbp/episodes/guide|website=BBC|accessdate=29 September 2017}}</ref>
# {{Timeline-event |date={{Start date|2016|09|27|df=y}} |event= [[Swansea]] - a 17th century work by [[Jacob Jordaens]]. }}<ref name="Jordaens" /> # {{Timeline-event |date={{Start date|2016|10|03|df=y}} |event= [[Aberdeenshire]] - a [[Madonna (art)|Madonna]] attributed "After [[Raphael]]". }} # {{Timeline-event |date={{Start date|2016|10|05|df=y}} |event= [[Belfast]] - works by [[Pieter Brueghel the Younger]]. }}
== Series 2 ==
Series two was aired in September–October 2017.
# {{Timeline-event|date={{Start date|2017|09|29|df=y}} |event= [[Glasgow]] - a portrait of [[George Villiers, 1st Duke of Buckingham]], at [[Pollok House]], is shown to be by [[Peter Paul Rubens]]. }}<ref name="O'Connor">{{cite news|last1=O'Connor|first1=Roisin|title=Lost Rubens portrait of one of the 'most famous gay men in history' rediscovered in Glasgow|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/art/news/rubens-painting-discovered-george-villiers-james-i-duke-of-buckinham-art-bbc-britains-lost-a7965486.html|accessdate=29 September 2017|work=[[The Independent]]|date=25 September 2017}}</ref> # {{Timeline-event|date={{Start date|2017|10|05|df=y}} |event= [[Derby]] - a potential hidden masterpiece by [[Joseph Wright of Derby]]. }} # {{Timeline-event|date={{Start date|2017|10|11|df=y}} |event= [[Carmarthenshire]]. }} # {{Timeline-event|date={{Start date|2017|10|18|df=y}} |event= [[Arbroath]]. A portrait by [[Antonis Mor]], from the collection of [[Hospitalfield House]], and previously owned by [[Patrick Allan Fraser]]. }}
